**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (based on the image provided)

**Location of Damage:**
- The front fender of the vehicle shows significant damage.
- There is a large crack running diagonally across the fender, starting from near the wheel well and extending towards the headlight area.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be structural, likely caused by a collision or impact that has resulted in a deep dent and a visible crack in the metal.
- The paint is chipped and scratched along the crack, indicating that the damage extends beyond just the surface layer.
- There is also some evidence of rust at the base of the crack, suggesting that the metal may have been compromised and exposed to moisture over time.

**Additional Notes:**
- The tape applied to the crack might be used as a temporary measure to prevent further damage or to stabilize the area before repair.
- The condition of the tire and wheel well also indicates that the vehicle has been involved in an incident, as the tire appears to be slightly damaged or misaligned.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained significant damage to the front fender, which requires professional repair to ensure safety and functionality. Further inspection may be necessary to assess any additional damage to other parts of the vehicle.
